t Bhilsa (near Vidisha). These caskets have been dated to the early 2nd century BCE, and the inscription states that the monks are of the Himalayan school. The missions may have set out from Vidisha in central India, as the caskets were discovered there, and as Mahinda is said to have stayed there for a month before setting out for Sri Lanka.", "annotations": [{"surface": "Erich Frauwallner", "start": 24, "end": 41, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erich_Frauwallner", "source": "a"}, {"surface": "Richard Gombrich", "start": 46, "end": 62, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Gombrich", "source": "a"}, {"surface": "Vinaya Nidana", "start": 242, "end": 255, "uri": "https://calvoritmo.com/tfm/entity/5055bbf4-ccf5-4600-97d7-60e59914c557", "source": "i"}, {"surface": "Bhilsa", "start": 410, "end": 416, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bhilsa", "source": "a"}, {"surface": "Vidisha", "start": 423, "end": 430, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vidisha", "source": "a"}, {"surface": "Erich Frauwallner", "start": 24, "end": 41, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erich_Frauwallner", "source": "dbpedia_spotlight"}, {"surface": "Gombrich", "start": 54, "end": 62, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Gombrich", "source": "dbpedia_spotlight"}, {"surface": "Vinaya", "start": 242, "end": 248, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vinaya", "source": "dbpedia_spotlight"}, {"surface": "Himalayan", "start": 319, "end": 328, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Himalayas", "source": "dbpedia_spotlight"}, {"surface": "relic", "start": 387, "end": 392, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Relic", "source": "dbpedia_spotlight"}, {"surface": "Bhilsa", "start": 410, "end": 416, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vidisha", "source": "dbpedia_spotlight"}, {"surface": "Vidisha", "start": 423, "end": 430, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vidisha", "source": "dbpedia_spotlight"}, {"surface": "BCE", "start": 488, "end": 491, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era", "so