subsequently, another order to kill all the Ajivikas in Pundravardhana. Around 18,000 followers of the Ajivika sect were executed as a result of this order. Sometime later, another Nirgrantha follower in Pataliputra drew a similar picture. Ashoka burnt him and his entire family alive in their house. He also announced an award of one dinara (gold coin) to anyone who brought him the head of a Nirgrantha heretic. According to Ashokavadana, as a result of this order, his own brother was mistaken for a heretic and killed by a cowherd. Ashoka realised his mistake, and withdrew the order.", "annotations": [{"surface": "Ashokavadana", "start": 17, "end": 29, "uri": "https://calvoritmo.com/tfm/entity/32cb4871-f8ff-45cb-8abb-803f2a284b4b", "source": "i"}, {"surface": "Pundravardhana", "start": 49, "end": 63, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pundravardhana", "source": "a"}, {"surface": "Mahavira", "start": 320, "end": 328, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mahavira", "source": "a"}, {"surface": "Jainism", "start": 350, "end": 357, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jainism", "source": "a"}, {"surface": "Ajivikas", "start": 526, "end": 534, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ajivika", "source": "a"}, {"surface": "Pataliputra", "start": 686, "end": 697, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pataliputra", "source": "a"}, {"surface": "dinara", "start": 817, "end": 823, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kushan_coinage", "source": "a"}, {"surface": "Ashokavadana", "start": 909, "end": 921, "uri": "https://calvoritmo.com/tfm/entity/46d6bef4-f4c1-4ff4-9100-b2a079830134", "source": "i"}, {"surface": "Ashokavadana", "start": 17, "end": 29, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashokavadana", "source": "dbpedia_spotlight"}, {"surface": "Pundravardhana", "start": 49, "end": 63, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pundravardhana", "source": "dbpedia_spotlight"}, {"surface": "Buddha", "start": 91, "end": 97, "uri": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gautama_Buddha", "source": "dbpedia_spotli